        <h1>Easy Meal Prep Ideas for the Week</h1>
        <p>Meal prepping is one of the most effective ways to maintain a healthy diet, save time, and avoid unhealthy food choices. By preparing meals in advance, you can ensure balanced nutrition, control portion sizes, and reduce the temptation of fast food...</p>
        <p>One of the biggest benefits of meal prep is the ability to plan well-balanced meals. When meals are prepared in advance, it's easier to incorporate the right balance of protein, carbohydrates, and healthy fats...</p>
        <p>Here are five meal prep ideas for a balanced week:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Overnight Oats with Chia Seeds and Berries</strong> – A quick, nutritious breakfast option that requires no cooking.</li>
            <li><strong>Grilled Chicken and Quinoa Bowls</strong> – A high-protein meal that can be paired with roasted vegetables.</li>
            <li><strong>Vegan Lentil Soup</strong> – A fiber-rich meal that can be stored for several days.</li>
            <li><strong>Turkey and Avocado Wraps</strong> – A low-carb, high-protein option for busy days.</li>
            <li><strong>Greek Yogurt and Almond Butter Parfaits</strong> – A great snack packed with protein and healthy fats.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>By planning meals ahead, you can stick to a healthy diet while saving time and effort in the kitchen...</p>
